article.headline: Northern Iowa 51, Drake 49
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Brooks McKowen made two free throws with 1.9 seconds left to give Northern Iowa a 51-49 victory over Drake on Saturday, keeping the Panthers in first place in the Missouri Valley Conference. McKowen was fouled by Al Stewart on a 3-point shot. He swished the first shot, was short on the second and made the third after Northern Iowa (19-3, 9-2 MVC) called a timeout. Drake (11-11, 4-7) got the ball in the frontcourt to Sean Tracy, who missed from 40 feet at the buzzer. Northern Iowa won for the fifth straight time despite getting outrebounded 44-31, shooting 23.5 percent from 3-point range and missing 13 of 24 free throws. Just a week ago, the Panthers shot 67 percent in beating Drake 91-72 at home. Ben Jacobson led the Panthers with 14 points, Grant Stout scored 13 and Eric Coleman 10. Stewart led Drake with 14 points. The Bulldogs shot only 33 percent and were just 5-for-11 from the free throw line. In a seesaw game, Northern Iowa led by 10 in the first half and Drake led by six in the second half. The Panthers pulled ahead 46-41 when Stout scored on a lob pass from Jacobson, but Drake came back to tie it twice, the second time at 49 when Stewart drove for a basket with 20.1 seconds remaining. Jacobson then controlled the ball for the Panthers and appeared to start making a move to the basket from the left side. Then he fired the ball across the court to McKowen, who was 0-for-5 on 3s and had missed seven straight shots. McKowen took the shot and Stewart got his hand on the ball, but the foul was called.
